1
00:00:20,240 --> 00:00:22,640
(SNORING)

2
00:00:35,880 --> 00:00:37,760
(ALARM BEEPING)

3
00:00:37,960 --> 00:00:40,520
AUTOMATED VOICE: Incoming salvage.
Please validate.

4
00:00:41,240 --> 00:00:43,920
Incoming salvage. Please validate.

5
00:00:44,480 --> 00:00:47,120
Incoming salvage. Please validate.

6
00:00:47,640 --> 00:00:50,680
-Incoming salvage. Please validate.
-(SIGHS)

7
00:00:51,040 --> 00:00:54,320
Rusty garbage.
It's not worth lacing up my boots.

8
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:57,280
Wasting our time.
There's no salvage this far out.

9
00:00:57,360 --> 00:01:00,120
You're a lucky boy, Tricky.
You're an android.

10
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:01,800
You don't get bored.

11
00:01:03,520 --> 00:01:05,800
He won't turn back.
Not with half a cargo.

12
00:01:05,880 --> 00:01:08,520
He's not captain. We're equal partners.

13
00:01:08,600 --> 00:01:10,800
Yeah. Right.

14
00:01:13,840 --> 00:01:15,560
-You said...
-I know what I said.

15
00:01:15,640 --> 00:01:16,840
I was the one who said it.

16
00:01:16,920 --> 00:01:18,320
You said it was looking at you funny.

17
00:01:18,400 --> 00:01:20,680
I was tired. Overwrought.
I didn't mean it.

18
00:01:20,760 --> 00:01:22,360
It's an appliance, it does a job.

19
00:01:22,440 --> 00:01:26,120
Yes, pretty cool appliance.
We're not talking cheese grater here.

20
00:01:26,200 --> 00:01:28,920
You're not getting me to talk
to your ship, that's properly bonkers.

21
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:30,080
(WHISPERS) It's okay, it's okay.

22
00:01:30,160 --> 00:01:31,360
Oh, you're like one of those guys

23
00:01:31,440 --> 00:01:33,280
who can't go out with a girl
unless his mother approves.

24
00:01:33,360 --> 00:01:36,480
It's important to me you get along.
I can leave you two alone together.

25
00:01:36,560 --> 00:01:37,720
Now you're creeping me out.

26
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:39,080
Take the wheel. Not the wheel.

27
00:01:39,160 --> 00:01:41,640
I'll make it easy.
Shut it down to basic mode for you.

28
00:01:41,720 --> 00:01:43,120
Basic?

29
00:01:43,200 --> 00:01:45,480
-'Cause I'm a girl?
-No.

30
00:01:50,280 --> 00:01:53,280
Everyone suit up. It's good salvage.

31
00:01:53,360 --> 00:01:55,160
-I can smell it.
-It's just trash.

32
00:01:55,240 --> 00:01:58,400
No, look. There's something tasty
in the Magoo field.

33
00:01:58,680 --> 00:02:00,440
(BEEPING)

34
00:02:02,800 --> 00:02:05,840
AUTOMATED VOICE: Magoo-Grab ready.
Engaging.

35
00:02:07,040 --> 00:02:08,960
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

36
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:13,080
Move yourself!

37
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:29,160
(TARDIS POWERING DOWN)

38
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:31,400
What have I done?

39
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:34,400
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

40
00:02:34,880 --> 00:02:37,120
Uh... Okay.

41
00:02:38,880 --> 00:02:40,240
(BEEPING)

42
00:02:44,920 --> 00:02:46,320
Doctor?

43
00:02:48,160 --> 00:02:51,640
The electrical impulses are jammed.
I can't get the shields back up.

44
00:02:51,720 --> 00:02:54,200
(GRUNTS) She's completely vulnerable.

45
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:55,960
I swear, I just touched it.

46
00:02:58,360 --> 00:03:01,800
Magnetic Hubble field!
We're flying right into it.

47
00:03:03,080 --> 00:03:05,120
Clara! Stay by me!

48
00:03:05,920 --> 00:03:08,000
Please tell me there's a button
you can press to fix this.

49
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:09,840
Oh, yes. Big friendly button.

50
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:11,760
-You're lying.
-Yeah.

51
00:03:11,840 --> 00:03:13,000
To stop me freaking out?

52
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:14,880
-Is it working?
-Not so much!

53
00:03:23,360 --> 00:03:24,440
Ow!

54
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:27,760
(SCREAMS)

55
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:29,920
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

56
00:04:09,760 --> 00:04:10,960
What is it?

57
00:04:11,040 --> 00:04:13,520
-Some kind of escape pod?
-Come on.

58
00:04:23,080 --> 00:04:24,440
Crack it open.

59
00:04:28,400 --> 00:04:29,880
(GRUNTING)

60
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:45,880
It's doing nothing.

61
00:04:45,960 --> 00:04:47,720
Use a thermo charge and blast it.

62
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:49,800
No, no, no! Wait!

63
00:04:49,880 --> 00:04:52,080
It's like, it's alive. She's...

64
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:53,720
(WARBLING)

65
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:55,560
She's... She's suffering.

66
00:04:56,280 --> 00:04:59,240
-I can feel it, I can feel it!
-It's just a robot, Bram.

67
00:04:59,320 --> 00:05:02,040
No, Gregor, he's right.
Looks like there's a broken fuel line.

68
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:04,120
All right. All right, throw it back.

69
00:05:04,200 --> 00:05:06,360
No salvage today, boys.
Open the bay doors.

70
00:05:06,720 --> 00:05:08,000
Wait.

71
00:05:14,800 --> 00:05:16,200
TRICKY: Somebody's under that thing.

72
00:05:16,280 --> 00:05:18,680
The crew was still aboard
when we dragged her in.

73
00:05:19,040 --> 00:05:21,160
We did nothing. If anyone asks, right,

74
00:05:21,240 --> 00:05:23,240
the ship was already busted.
You got that?

75
00:05:23,320 --> 00:05:25,800
And you, make sure you keep
your oily mouth shut. All right?

76
00:05:25,880 --> 00:05:27,560
It's rude to whisper.

77
00:05:28,280 --> 00:05:31,800
Hi. I'm The Doctor. And you are...

78
00:05:32,880 --> 00:05:35,400
Van Baalen and...

79
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:37,720
Van Baalen.

80
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:39,600
Van Baalen and Van Baalen.

81
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:41,360
That's going to get confusing later.

82
00:05:42,080 --> 00:05:43,280
We found you drifting.

83
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:46,560
Yeah, your ship was
junked up pretty bad.

84
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:49,120
What broke my ship was a Magoo-Grab.

85
00:05:50,320 --> 00:05:52,240
I found this remote in your pocket. Eh?

86
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:55,320
What are the chances?
Outlawed in most galaxies,

87
00:05:55,400 --> 00:05:58,840
this little beasty
can disable whole vessels.

88
00:05:58,920 --> 00:06:01,240
Unless you have shield oscillators,

89
00:06:01,320 --> 00:06:05,360
which I turned off so Clara could fly.

90
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:08,320
Dammit!

91
00:06:09,680 --> 00:06:11,680
Clara! Where is she?

92
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:16,000
A girl about so high, feisty.

93
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:20,560
She's still on board.

94
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:23,600
No, wait! Your pod is leaking fuel.

95
00:06:23,960 --> 00:06:27,200
If she's still in there, she's dead.

96
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:28,840
Oh.

97
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:33,440
Ah. Respirators.

98
00:06:33,520 --> 00:06:36,080
We can open the doors for a split
second, reach in and grab her.

99
00:06:36,160 --> 00:06:38,960
Trust me, we can't.
Now, please. Help me get her out.

100
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:41,680
-I'm telling you, she...
-Shut it, tin mouth!

101
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:44,480
What sort of fee are we talking?

102
00:06:44,960 --> 00:06:48,000
If you help me get her out,
you get the machine, all the scrap.

103
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:49,800
-Eh?
-It's not worth the risk.

104
00:06:49,880 --> 00:06:51,720
Four feet of metal? No.

105
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:53,920
What if I can guarantee you
the best haul you've ever had?

106
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:55,520
Bram, open the bay doors.

107
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:57,720
No, no, please, stop. Listen, listen.

108
00:06:58,640 --> 00:07:02,560
Right behind those doors
is the salvage of a lifetime.

109
00:07:19,040 --> 00:07:20,440
Doctor?

110
00:07:23,160 --> 00:07:24,400
(GRUNTS)

111
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:32,000
Doctor?

112
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:37,960
(GROANS)

113
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:42,720
(BLOWING)

114
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:47,880
(ALARM BEEPING)

115
00:07:58,360 --> 00:07:59,840
Red flashing light.

116
00:08:01,360 --> 00:08:03,120
Means something bad.

117
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:05,480
"Get out of here fast"?

118
00:08:05,880 --> 00:08:08,640
Or possibly "whatever you do,
don't open this door".

119
00:08:15,560 --> 00:08:16,720
Bad decision.

120
00:08:40,560 --> 00:08:42,280
(SNARLING)

121
00:08:44,520 --> 00:08:46,640
Hey, are we really going to risk it?

122
00:08:46,720 --> 00:08:49,960
That thing is spewing poison.
Should blow it back into space.

123
00:08:50,040 --> 00:08:51,760
-Get your gear.
-Hey.

124
00:08:51,840 --> 00:08:54,160
I don't take orders from my kid brother.

125
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:57,880
Don't try and form sentences, all right?
Stick to what you do best.

126
00:09:02,240 --> 00:09:06,040
Tell me, since when does an android
need a blast suit and a respirator?

127
00:09:06,120 --> 00:09:09,280
Flesh coating.
Same as us, he'd burn up.

128
00:09:10,520 --> 00:09:12,600
No fear, no heat, no pain.

129
00:09:22,400 --> 00:09:23,760
Salvage of a lifetime?

130
00:09:23,840 --> 00:09:26,400
I feel pretty confident
I can deliver on that.

131
00:09:26,480 --> 00:09:28,000
Here we go!

132
00:09:32,040 --> 00:09:35,000
I don't get it.
Thought she was lying on her side.

133
00:09:35,680 --> 00:09:38,080
The Tardis is special.
She has her own gravity.

134
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:40,760
I'd explain if I had some charts
and a board pen.

135
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:42,720
It's, it's...

136
00:09:43,240 --> 00:09:44,960
-It's bigger.
-On the inside.

137
00:09:45,040 --> 00:09:46,960
You know, I get that a lot.

138
00:09:47,040 --> 00:09:49,320
Whoa! Awesome.

139
00:09:49,400 --> 00:09:51,480
Well put. "Whoa" and "awesome".

140
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:56,920
Safe to breathe.

141
00:09:57,920 --> 00:09:59,880
Okay, now,

142
00:10:00,840 --> 00:10:02,840
the last thing I remember,
you were right here.

143
00:10:03,520 --> 00:10:06,600
Come on, Clara. Talk to me.

144
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:08,880
How big is this baby?

145
00:10:08,960 --> 00:10:10,960
Picture the biggest ship
you've ever seen.

146
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:12,680
-Are you picturing it?
-Yeah.

147
00:10:12,760 --> 00:10:15,480
Good. Now forget it,
because this ship is infinite.

148
00:10:16,120 --> 00:10:17,440
Take you hours to find the girl.

149
00:10:17,520 --> 00:10:20,680
Days. Plus this whole place is toxic.
She'd be dead by the time I reach her.

150
00:10:20,760 --> 00:10:23,800
So, here's the mission.
We're going to find her in one hour.

151
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:26,000
-We?
-You're my guys for this.

152
00:10:26,080 --> 00:10:27,640
-That wasn't the deal.
-It is now.

153
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:28,960
What makes you think we'll help?

154
00:10:30,040 --> 00:10:32,840
I just activated
the Tardis self-destruct system.

155
00:10:35,040 --> 00:10:36,840
One hour until this ship blows.

156
00:10:37,760 --> 00:10:40,480
Don't try to leave.
The Tardis is in lockdown.

157
00:10:40,560 --> 00:10:42,600
I'll open those doors
when Clara's by my side.

158
00:10:42,680 --> 00:10:44,000
You crazy lunatic!

159
00:10:44,080 --> 00:10:45,960
My ship! My rules!

160
00:10:46,040 --> 00:10:47,520
You'll kill us all. And the girl.

161
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:49,240
She's going to die
if you don't help me.

162
00:10:49,320 --> 00:10:51,240
Don't get into a spaceship
with a madman.

163
00:10:51,320 --> 00:10:53,000
Didn't anyone ever teach you that?

164
00:10:53,960 --> 00:10:56,240
Okay. A little gentle persuasion.

165
00:10:57,120 --> 00:10:58,280
Say 30 minutes.

166
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:01,840
We'll die even quicker now!

167
00:11:01,920 --> 00:11:03,920
We all perform better under pressure.

168
00:11:04,280 --> 00:11:07,000
-Anybody want to go for 15 minutes?
-ALL: Whoa!

169
00:11:08,160 --> 00:11:10,080
It's your own time you're wasting.

170
00:11:11,080 --> 00:11:12,760
Salvage of a lifetime.

171
00:11:13,960 --> 00:11:15,280
You meant the ship,

172
00:11:16,120 --> 00:11:17,360
I meant Clara.

173
00:11:55,840 --> 00:11:57,800
(CREATURE GROWLING, CLARA GASPS)

174
00:12:04,320 --> 00:12:05,680
Report.

175
00:12:06,160 --> 00:12:07,600
What's on board this thing?

176
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:10,880
AUTOMATED VOICE: Dynamorphic generators.
Conceptual geometer.

177
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:14,600
Beam synthesiser.
Orthogonal engine filters.

178
00:12:18,040 --> 00:12:19,680
Guys, guys, look.

179
00:12:19,760 --> 00:12:21,320
I think we should split up.

180
00:12:21,400 --> 00:12:22,960
It's our best chance
of finding the girl.

181
00:12:23,040 --> 00:12:24,280
You know it is.

182
00:12:26,440 --> 00:12:29,120
Don't touch a thing.
The Tardis will get huffy if you mess.

183
00:12:30,040 --> 00:12:31,840
Keep in radio contact, all right?

184
00:12:34,200 --> 00:12:36,400
Get back to the console. Strip it apart.

185
00:12:36,720 --> 00:12:37,920
-Okay.
-All right?

186
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:44,520
(GROWLING)

187
00:13:02,760 --> 00:13:04,800
(CREATURE SNARLING)

188
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:23,880
Now, that's just showing off.

189
00:13:42,440 --> 00:13:44,040
(GRUNTING)

190
00:13:49,760 --> 00:13:51,720
(PREVIOUS DOCTOR AND COMPANION
VOICES OVERLAPPING)

191
00:13:51,800 --> 00:13:53,960
WOMAN: ...Time And Relative Dimension
In Space.

192
00:13:54,040 --> 00:13:56,120
THIRD DOCTOR:
Dimensionally transcendental.

193
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:58,960
(OVERLAPPING VOICES CONTINUE)

194
00:13:59,840 --> 00:14:01,480
NINTH DOCTOR:
The assembled hordes of Genghis Khan

195
00:14:01,560 --> 00:14:04,480
couldn't get through that door.
Believe me, they've tried.

196
00:14:04,560 --> 00:14:07,280
AMY: We are in space!

197
00:14:07,800 --> 00:14:11,400
(OVERLAPPING VOICES CONTINUE,
INDISTINCT)

198
00:14:15,120 --> 00:14:16,880
(SENSOR BEEPING)

199
00:14:26,560 --> 00:14:27,680
AUTOMATED VOICE: Everything.

200
00:14:27,760 --> 00:14:29,040
What? Report.

201
00:14:29,560 --> 00:14:31,840
Everything behind that door.

202
00:14:32,520 --> 00:14:34,280
-Everything?
-Sensor detects

203
00:14:34,880 --> 00:14:37,040
everything you could possibly want.

204
00:14:46,840 --> 00:14:47,880
Everything.

205
00:14:48,280 --> 00:14:50,560
I don't understand. Give me a price tag.

206
00:14:50,640 --> 00:14:51,840
Incalculable.

207
00:14:51,920 --> 00:14:52,960
What?

208
00:14:53,040 --> 00:14:56,200
More valuable than
the total sum of any currency.

209
00:14:56,680 --> 00:14:59,320
Living metal. Bespoke engineering.

210
00:14:59,760 --> 00:15:03,560
Whatever machine you require,
this system will build it.

211
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:11,440
(GASPS)

212
00:15:14,200 --> 00:15:16,120
No! No, no, stop. Please.

213
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:18,120
Don't... Don't touch it.

214
00:15:18,440 --> 00:15:20,760
Please. She won't let you touch it.

215
00:15:21,600 --> 00:15:23,800
I can feel a Tardis tantrum coming on.

216
00:15:24,320 --> 00:15:25,680
What the hell is this place?

217
00:15:25,760 --> 00:15:28,080
Architectural reconfiguration system.

218
00:15:28,160 --> 00:15:30,680
It reconstructs particles
according to your needs.

219
00:15:30,760 --> 00:15:32,080
A machine that makes machines?

220
00:15:32,160 --> 00:15:34,000
Yes. Basically.

221
00:15:37,080 --> 00:15:38,160
What are you doing?

222
00:15:38,240 --> 00:15:39,600
No, no. Don't, don't!

223
00:15:39,680 --> 00:15:41,120
If you walk out of here
with that circuit,

224
00:15:41,200 --> 00:15:43,280
the Tardis will try to stop you.
Now, listen to me.

225
00:15:44,240 --> 00:15:46,760
Look, the clock is ticking.
We must find Clara.

226
00:15:48,760 --> 00:15:51,960
(HIGH-PITCHED TONE BLARING)

227
00:15:52,840 --> 00:15:54,360
What the...

228
00:15:55,480 --> 00:15:57,120
Where's the door gone?

229
00:15:57,600 --> 00:15:59,040
Ever seen a spaceship get ugly?

230
00:15:59,320 --> 00:16:00,680
This isn't happening.

231
00:16:00,760 --> 00:16:02,160
DOCTOR: She won't relinquish it.

232
00:16:02,960 --> 00:16:04,680
Her basic genetic material.

233
00:16:05,440 --> 00:16:06,640
Torch it.

234
00:16:07,280 --> 00:16:08,440
I said torch it.

235
00:16:08,520 --> 00:16:10,400
Can't you feel it, Gregor? The ship...

236
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:13,280
The ship's in torment.
Like it's a living thing.

237
00:16:13,360 --> 00:16:14,960
You can't hurt it.

238
00:16:20,640 --> 00:16:23,600
What's the matter, Tardis?
Scared to fight me?

239
00:16:50,360 --> 00:16:51,720
So that's who...

240
00:16:51,800 --> 00:16:54,280
(DOOR CLANGS, CREATURE GROWLING)

241
00:17:15,600 --> 00:17:17,040
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

242
00:17:17,360 --> 00:17:19,960
(VOICES ECHOING, MUFFLED AND INDISTINCT)

243
00:17:21,880 --> 00:17:23,480
(GROWLING CONTINUES)

244
00:17:27,240 --> 00:17:29,760
(OVERLAPPING VOICES, INDISTINCT)

245
00:17:36,280 --> 00:17:37,880
(LOW GROWLING)

246
00:17:43,520 --> 00:17:45,880
(GROWLING)

247
00:18:15,640 --> 00:18:17,360
It's the same. It's just the same.

248
00:18:19,080 --> 00:18:20,760
It's diverting us.

249
00:18:20,840 --> 00:18:24,760
Spinning a maze around us.
We will never reach Clara in time.

250
00:18:26,240 --> 00:18:27,840
Hey! Hey!

251
00:18:32,960 --> 00:18:34,480
It's just the same, again.

252
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:37,120
No point in building walls,
you'll just know how to smash them down.

253
00:18:37,200 --> 00:18:38,840
It's found other ways
of controlling you.

254
00:18:38,920 --> 00:18:40,640
Smart bunch, Time Lords.

255
00:18:40,720 --> 00:18:43,760
No dress sense,
dreadful hats, but smart.

256
00:18:45,200 --> 00:18:49,200
If you want to get out of here,
let that circuit go.

257
00:18:50,480 --> 00:18:53,080
It is creating a labyrinth.

258
00:18:53,400 --> 00:18:55,280
Bram. Bram, can you hear me?

259
00:18:55,360 --> 00:18:57,480
TRICKY: Bram, the ship is alive.
Get out of there.

260
00:18:57,560 --> 00:18:59,080
Bram, don't touch anything.

261
00:18:59,160 --> 00:19:01,240
You're just the sweetest thing ever.

262
00:19:09,760 --> 00:19:11,360
Oh, thank you. (LAUGHS)

263
00:19:11,440 --> 00:19:13,760
Thank you, thank you,
thank you, thank you!

264
00:19:14,360 --> 00:19:15,560
(LAUGHING)

265
00:19:15,880 --> 00:19:17,000
Oh!

266
00:19:19,320 --> 00:19:20,560
No.

267
00:19:21,880 --> 00:19:23,240
The door.

268
00:19:23,720 --> 00:19:25,440
Where has the door gone now?

269
00:19:27,200 --> 00:19:28,440
You can't do this!

270
00:19:28,840 --> 00:19:31,120
Bram, you've got to get out of there.
Come on.

271
00:19:31,200 --> 00:19:32,680
(SPARKING)

272
00:19:33,120 --> 00:19:34,520
(GRUNTS)

273
00:19:39,760 --> 00:19:41,000
(COUGHS)

274
00:19:43,520 --> 00:19:44,800
(GROWLING)

275
00:19:45,840 --> 00:19:47,360
(COUGHING)

276
00:19:51,320 --> 00:19:52,680
(GROWLING CONTINUES)

277
00:19:53,200 --> 00:19:54,760
(SCREAMING)

278
00:20:00,120 --> 00:20:01,720
(BRAM SCREAMING)

279
00:20:01,840 --> 00:20:04,320
-Channel's dead.
-You've got to help him.

280
00:20:04,720 --> 00:20:06,800
Gregor, do something. Do something!

281
00:20:06,880 --> 00:20:10,240
It's too late. He's gone.
Just worry about the salvage.

282
00:20:10,320 --> 00:20:12,160
You care more about a circuit
than you do about him.

283
00:20:12,240 --> 00:20:14,680
Your concern for your brother
is really touching.

284
00:20:14,760 --> 00:20:16,320
The android is more cut up
about it than you are.

285
00:20:16,400 --> 00:20:18,720
Now, will you two
stop bickering and listen!

286
00:20:18,800 --> 00:20:21,080
There is something else down there.

287
00:20:21,160 --> 00:20:22,720
(CREATURE HISSING)

288
00:20:26,760 --> 00:20:27,920
We've got to get out of here.

289
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:29,520
Gregor, give it back.

290
00:20:29,600 --> 00:20:31,480
-Give it back to her.
-What are you doing?

291
00:20:31,560 --> 00:20:33,200
You're always on the side
of the machines.

292
00:20:33,280 --> 00:20:34,840
Fellas!

293
00:20:35,480 --> 00:20:39,280
Multiple life forms on board the Tardis
with us, I am getting a massive signal.

294
00:20:39,360 --> 00:20:42,560
-Where are they?
-You're not going to like the answer.

295
00:20:42,640 --> 00:20:45,680
-(WHISPERS) About two steps away.
-(GROWLING)

296
00:20:45,760 --> 00:20:48,200
One step.

297
00:20:51,520 --> 00:20:52,800
(ALL SCREAMING)

298
00:20:55,440 --> 00:20:57,600
Tricky! Look out! Careful!

299
00:20:59,880 --> 00:21:02,240
Gregor! No!

300
00:21:02,440 --> 00:21:04,560
We have to stay together! Come on, go!

301
00:21:04,840 --> 00:21:06,200
Tricky! Come on!

302
00:21:08,960 --> 00:21:10,280
I'm sorry.

303
00:21:58,520 --> 00:22:00,560
Oh, why are you doing this?

304
00:22:06,760 --> 00:22:08,480
Back where we started?

305
00:22:08,560 --> 00:22:09,840
No.

306
00:22:10,440 --> 00:22:12,200
It's an echo.

307
00:22:14,040 --> 00:22:16,480
The console room.
It's the safest place on the ship.

308
00:22:16,560 --> 00:22:18,440
It could replicate itself
any number of times.

309
00:22:18,520 --> 00:22:19,840
It's trying to protect us.

310
00:22:19,920 --> 00:22:21,640
Because I tried to give back
the circuit?

311
00:22:21,720 --> 00:22:23,040
Team Tardis.

312
00:22:28,360 --> 00:22:30,000
Where did... Where did that go?

313
00:22:30,080 --> 00:22:33,560
There's more than one echo room.
Hey, look. Look!

314
00:22:36,080 --> 00:22:39,040
The Tardis has got Clara safe.
That was her. That was her there.

315
00:22:39,120 --> 00:22:41,280
Thank you! Thank you! Thank you!

316
00:22:41,360 --> 00:22:43,280
But why... Why can't we see her?

317
00:22:43,360 --> 00:22:44,760
Well, it's like a light switch.

318
00:22:44,840 --> 00:22:46,280
Two positions.
(MIMICKING SWITCHES CLICKING)

319
00:22:46,360 --> 00:22:49,080
Flickering at super infinite speeds.
We're only together for a brief second.

320
00:22:49,160 --> 00:22:51,400
(SWITCH FLICKS, CLARA GASPS)

321
00:22:53,880 --> 00:22:54,960
Shh.

322
00:22:57,320 --> 00:22:58,760
(CLARA PANTING)

323
00:22:59,480 --> 00:23:00,720
I can hear her.

324
00:23:11,560 --> 00:23:13,320
(CREATURE SNARLING, CLARA GASPS)

325
00:23:14,520 --> 00:23:16,520
(SCREAMING)

326
00:23:18,800 --> 00:23:21,600
She's let it in. She's let it in!

327
00:23:21,720 --> 00:23:24,320
(CREATURE GROWLING)

328
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:38,200
Ah. If I can just isolate her position,

329
00:23:38,280 --> 00:23:41,680
I could match your connection,
reach in and grab her.

330
00:23:47,080 --> 00:23:48,520
What are you?

331
00:23:50,080 --> 00:23:53,240
AUTOMATED VOICE: Console room.
Echo imprint of the original.

332
00:23:53,320 --> 00:23:56,160
You're coming with me.
I need you to get me out of here.

333
00:23:56,240 --> 00:23:59,360
-(SCREWDRIVER WHIRRING)
-Scanning for female human.

334
00:24:07,520 --> 00:24:09,760
Scanning for female human.

335
00:24:13,400 --> 00:24:15,120
Unidentified human.

336
00:24:15,440 --> 00:24:17,040
-It doesn't know Lancashire.
-What?

337
00:24:17,120 --> 00:24:20,120
It doesn't know sass.
Yes! It's found Clara!

338
00:24:20,200 --> 00:24:23,240
-It's found her. She is right there.
- (CLARA SCREAMING)

339
00:24:23,360 --> 00:24:24,880
(CREATURE SNARLING)

340
00:24:29,160 --> 00:24:31,160
It's okay. Clara, I'm so, so sorry.

341
00:24:31,240 --> 00:24:33,280
Sorry. Please, please forgive me, Clara.

342
00:24:33,360 --> 00:24:36,600
Ow! Okay. So we're not doing hugging.
I get that now.

343
00:24:36,680 --> 00:24:37,960
What do you keep in here?

344
00:24:38,040 --> 00:24:40,880
Why have you got zombie creatures?
Good guys do not have zombie creatures.

345
00:24:40,960 --> 00:24:43,760
-Rule one, basic storytelling!
-Not in front of the guests.

346
00:24:45,280 --> 00:24:47,000
-Who are they?
-Friends.

347
00:24:47,080 --> 00:24:48,760
Well, people who aren't
trying to kill us.

348
00:24:48,840 --> 00:24:50,480
I don't need punching again.

349
00:24:50,560 --> 00:24:52,960
All right, all right. Look,
a deal's a deal. You got the girl back.

350
00:24:53,040 --> 00:24:56,000
-Now, cancel the self-destruct.
-Ah! Ah.

351
00:24:56,320 --> 00:24:59,720
Ha! You know, I've got to tell you,

352
00:24:59,800 --> 00:25:02,640
-I won't be needing you in my quiz team.
-What?

353
00:25:02,920 --> 00:25:04,840
There is no self-destruct.

354
00:25:04,920 --> 00:25:08,960
Hey? Hey? Hey?
Had you going, though, boys, didn't I?

355
00:25:09,040 --> 00:25:12,320
I just wiggled a few buttons.
Yeah, the old wiggly button trick.

356
00:25:12,400 --> 00:25:16,560
And the face. You've got to do the face.
"Save her or we all die."

357
00:25:17,600 --> 00:25:20,440
-I thought I rushed it a bit but...
-So, you're telling us we're safe?

358
00:25:20,520 --> 00:25:22,400
Ish, apart from the monsters

359
00:25:22,480 --> 00:25:24,760
and the Tardis reinventing
the architecture every five minutes.

360
00:25:24,840 --> 00:25:27,760
Guys, don't worry.
The countdown's a fake.

361
00:25:27,840 --> 00:25:30,120
Look, just give me a second,
I'll turn it off.

362
00:25:30,600 --> 00:25:34,560
I only made it look as though the engine
was actually exploding.

363
00:25:35,120 --> 00:25:36,360
(ALARM BLARING)

364
00:25:36,440 --> 00:25:38,640
Ah. Okay, that's not good.

365
00:25:40,360 --> 00:25:42,960
Okay, don't panic. Well, maybe panic.

366
00:25:46,000 --> 00:25:48,040
Something you want to share
with the rest of us?

367
00:25:48,120 --> 00:25:53,440
It appears the engine is damaged.
We're in trouble, Clara. Proper trouble.

368
00:25:54,120 --> 00:25:55,600
It needs fixing or we're toast.

369
00:25:55,680 --> 00:25:58,320
So, now would be a good time
to use that big friendly button, right?

370
00:25:58,400 --> 00:25:59,880
Yes. Sorry, I should have
had one built in.

371
00:25:59,960 --> 00:26:01,480
-TRICKY: Where are we going?
-Detour.

372
00:26:03,560 --> 00:26:04,840
The centre of the Tardis.

373
00:26:13,000 --> 00:26:14,600
-(CREATURE SNARLING)
-Shh.

374
00:26:15,880 --> 00:26:17,200
Something's in here.

375
00:26:17,280 --> 00:26:19,560
Those things, they followed us.

376
00:26:20,360 --> 00:26:23,880
Doctor, what are they?
What aren't you telling me?

377
00:26:23,960 --> 00:26:27,400
Trust me,
some things you don't want to know.

378
00:26:27,480 --> 00:26:29,040
(SNARLING)

379
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:31,400
They're on the move again.

380
00:26:31,480 --> 00:26:33,480
Run! Move! Move!

381
00:26:38,120 --> 00:26:39,640
(SNARLING)

382
00:26:41,400 --> 00:26:42,840
Doctor?

383
00:26:48,120 --> 00:26:49,560
Doctor!

384
00:26:50,200 --> 00:26:51,680
Again!

385
00:26:57,120 --> 00:26:58,360
(SIZZLING)

386
00:27:01,120 --> 00:27:03,400
CLARA: I know what I said.
I was the one who said it.

387
00:27:03,480 --> 00:27:05,240
DOCTOR: You said it was
looking at you funny.

388
00:27:06,760 --> 00:27:08,320
Now you're creeping me out.

389
00:27:09,920 --> 00:27:12,680
Please tell me there is a button
you can press to fix this?

390
00:27:15,600 --> 00:27:16,840
(GASPS) Oh, thank God.

391
00:27:18,720 --> 00:27:20,120
Doctor?

392
00:27:20,680 --> 00:27:22,160
What's going on?

393
00:27:24,840 --> 00:27:26,400
Say something.

394
00:27:26,760 --> 00:27:28,360
Clara, stop.

395
00:27:29,360 --> 00:27:30,840
Don't touch it.

396
00:27:33,200 --> 00:27:35,560
There's a rupture in time
somewhere on board this ship,

397
00:27:35,640 --> 00:27:38,600
a small tear
in the fabric of the continuum.

398
00:27:38,680 --> 00:27:41,720
It must have happened when the Tardis
was pulled in by the salvage vessel.

399
00:27:41,800 --> 00:27:43,880
-The Tardis is leaking.
-Leaking what?

400
00:27:43,960 --> 00:27:45,880
The past. You and me.

401
00:27:45,960 --> 00:27:48,400
Everything we've done,
everything we've said.

402
00:27:48,480 --> 00:27:50,120
Recent history.

403
00:27:50,200 --> 00:27:52,280
It's not real. It's a memory.

404
00:27:56,440 --> 00:27:57,680
What about this?

405
00:27:57,760 --> 00:27:59,600
If you're giving me the option,
I'd say this one's real.

406
00:27:59,680 --> 00:28:01,000
(GROWLING)

407
00:28:08,360 --> 00:28:10,560
-She's right onto us.
-She?

408
00:28:11,360 --> 00:28:13,600
Clara, don't ask me any more.

409
00:28:17,520 --> 00:28:19,800
CLARA: You're like one of those guys
who can't go out with a girl

410
00:28:19,880 --> 00:28:21,160
unless his mother approves.

411
00:28:21,240 --> 00:28:23,400
DOCTOR: It's important to me
you get along.

412
00:28:23,480 --> 00:28:25,440
I can leave you two alone together.

413
00:28:26,400 --> 00:28:28,280
(CLANGING)

414
00:28:31,200 --> 00:28:33,200
-What's that noise?
-(CREAKING)

415
00:28:33,680 --> 00:28:35,320
We're right under the primary fuel cell.

416
00:28:35,400 --> 00:28:36,880
So... So what?

417
00:28:36,960 --> 00:28:38,560
So... So...

418
00:28:39,040 --> 00:28:42,000
Well, the fuel's spilled out.
So the rods will be exposed.

419
00:28:42,080 --> 00:28:43,640
-Means they'll cool and...
-And start to warp.

420
00:28:43,720 --> 00:28:46,080
-And start to warp, maybe even...
-No, you don't say it.

421
00:28:46,160 --> 00:28:47,680
-Mmm.
-Don't you dare say it.

422
00:28:47,760 --> 00:28:50,440
Maybe even...break apart.

423
00:28:54,400 --> 00:28:56,400
-Run?
-I'm liking how you're thinking.

424
00:29:04,720 --> 00:29:06,480
(MAN SCREAMING)

425
00:29:07,640 --> 00:29:09,560
No, cut it off. Just cut my arm off.

426
00:29:09,640 --> 00:29:12,000
-No!
-It's the quickest way to release me.

427
00:29:12,080 --> 00:29:14,880
No fear. No, hate, no...no pain.

428
00:29:16,600 --> 00:29:19,040
I can get a new one. Disposable part.
Just do it.

429
00:29:20,520 --> 00:29:21,840
It won't hurt me.

430
00:29:22,200 --> 00:29:25,400
-Tricky, you don't understand.
-I'm an android, cut me!

431
00:29:25,480 --> 00:29:26,840
You made it through.

432
00:29:28,000 --> 00:29:30,240
What's the matter with you?
Why won't you cut me?

433
00:29:30,320 --> 00:29:31,760
(GROANING)

434
00:29:35,280 --> 00:29:36,720
Tell him.

435
00:29:37,640 --> 00:29:39,080
Tell me what?

436
00:29:40,680 --> 00:29:42,440
You can't, can you?

437
00:29:42,520 --> 00:29:43,920
You're a coward.

438
00:29:44,160 --> 00:29:46,440
You won't save him
but you're scared to tell him why.

439
00:29:46,520 --> 00:29:47,960
What's he going on about?

440
00:29:48,040 --> 00:29:50,120
Robots don't need blast suits,
they don't need respirators.

441
00:29:50,200 --> 00:29:53,440
They don't get frightened
of monsters in the dark.

442
00:29:53,520 --> 00:29:55,640
What's he talking about?

443
00:29:57,240 --> 00:29:59,720
Two bionic eyes
and a synthetic voice box.

444
00:30:00,520 --> 00:30:03,240
But you, my friend, are human.

445
00:30:03,320 --> 00:30:05,040
Flesh and blood.

446
00:30:06,360 --> 00:30:08,680
-It was a joke.
-What?

447
00:30:09,240 --> 00:30:11,200
It was just a stupid joke.

448
00:30:11,280 --> 00:30:14,120
-We did it to relieve the boredom.
-Well, it was very funny.

449
00:30:14,840 --> 00:30:16,480
They lied to you.

450
00:30:16,560 --> 00:30:20,200
Changed your identity, just to provide
some in-flight entertainment.

451
00:30:20,280 --> 00:30:21,560
I'm sorry.

452
00:30:22,800 --> 00:30:25,000
-(GROANS)
-You're human, Tricky.

453
00:30:26,480 --> 00:30:27,880
Cut the metal.

454
00:30:28,440 --> 00:30:30,720
-Cut the metal! Go!
-(TRICKY GROANING)

455
00:30:38,600 --> 00:30:40,080
GREGOR: Where are we?

456
00:30:40,840 --> 00:30:42,200
Power source.

457
00:30:42,280 --> 00:30:43,760
Right. You lot wait here,

458
00:30:43,840 --> 00:30:47,600
I'll check it's safe. We can only
survive for a minute or two in there.

459
00:30:47,680 --> 00:30:49,920
Um, what happens if we stay longer?

460
00:30:50,000 --> 00:30:52,640
Our cells will liquefy
and our skin will start to burn.

461
00:30:52,720 --> 00:30:54,680
I always feel so good
after we've spoken.

462
00:30:54,760 --> 00:30:57,480
-Marvellous. Keep this door shut.
-That will not be a problem.

463
00:31:05,160 --> 00:31:07,600
AUTOMATED VOICE:
Lancashire. Sass.

464
00:31:07,680 --> 00:31:09,360
Intelligent sensor.

465
00:31:09,440 --> 00:31:12,400
Ever pointed that thing at
yourself, Gregor? What would it see?

466
00:31:12,480 --> 00:31:14,680
What sort of person
does this to another human?

467
00:31:14,760 --> 00:31:17,160
Made them believe
they're made of metal.

468
00:31:17,240 --> 00:31:18,600
Who am I?

469
00:31:39,200 --> 00:31:40,720
(GROANING)

470
00:31:44,760 --> 00:31:46,800
My mouthy little kid brother.

471
00:31:48,040 --> 00:31:50,720
Why... Why don't I remember?

472
00:31:50,800 --> 00:31:54,160
It was a salvage accident.
Big explosion.

473
00:31:54,240 --> 00:31:56,920
You lost your sight, voice
and your memory.

474
00:31:57,000 --> 00:32:00,320
And you... You thought of a way
you could have some fun with me.

475
00:32:00,960 --> 00:32:02,760
I just wanted a brother beside me.

476
00:32:02,840 --> 00:32:05,080
You were always the smart one, Tricky.

477
00:32:06,560 --> 00:32:09,960
He wanted you to take over.
He made you Captain.

478
00:32:12,160 --> 00:32:13,440
He?

479
00:32:13,520 --> 00:32:14,880
Dad.

480
00:32:14,960 --> 00:32:18,240
I don't... I don't remember him.

481
00:32:24,240 --> 00:32:25,680
You did this to me

482
00:32:25,760 --> 00:32:28,440
just to be captain of a...
of a heap of junk?

483
00:32:30,360 --> 00:32:33,280
-CLARA: Stop!
-Tricky? Listen to me.

484
00:32:33,480 --> 00:32:35,120
Ask yourself why he couldn't cut you up.

485
00:32:35,200 --> 00:32:37,400
He has just one tiny scrap
of decency left in him

486
00:32:37,480 --> 00:32:39,280
and you helped him find that. Okay?

487
00:32:39,360 --> 00:32:42,840
Now, you... Don't ever forget this.

488
00:32:47,680 --> 00:32:49,520
Okay! Move, move, move!

489
00:32:52,360 --> 00:32:54,000
The Eye of Harmony.

490
00:32:54,080 --> 00:32:58,000
Exploding star, in the act
of becoming a black hole.

491
00:32:58,080 --> 00:32:59,640
Time Lord engineering.

492
00:32:59,720 --> 00:33:01,960
You rip the star from its orbit,

493
00:33:02,040 --> 00:33:04,520
suspend it
in a permanent state of decay.

494
00:33:04,600 --> 00:33:06,280
This way, quickly!

495
00:33:09,400 --> 00:33:10,800
(GROWLING)

496
00:33:23,160 --> 00:33:24,560
There's no way out, we're trapped.

497
00:33:24,840 --> 00:33:26,200
You're going to tell me right now!

498
00:33:26,280 --> 00:33:28,960
If we're going to die here
you're going to tell me what they are.

499
00:33:29,040 --> 00:33:30,680
-I can't.
-Tell me.

500
00:33:31,240 --> 00:33:32,640
What's the use of secrets now?

501
00:33:32,720 --> 00:33:35,760
Secrets protect us.
Secrets make us safe.

502
00:33:35,840 --> 00:33:37,320
We're not safe!

503
00:33:40,920 --> 00:33:43,480
AUTOMATED VOICE:
Sensor detects animal DNA.

504
00:33:43,560 --> 00:33:45,880
Human core element.

505
00:33:45,960 --> 00:33:48,720
Calculating data. Calculating data.

506
00:33:48,800 --> 00:33:50,560
No, no, turn it off!

507
00:33:51,200 --> 00:33:53,840
Lancashire. Sass.

508
00:33:55,320 --> 00:33:57,400
Identifiable substance.

509
00:33:57,480 --> 00:33:59,200
Clara.

510
00:34:05,720 --> 00:34:07,880
-That's me.
-I'm so sorry.

511
00:34:13,040 --> 00:34:15,880
That's me. I burn in here.

512
00:34:15,960 --> 00:34:19,680
It isn't just the past leaking out
through the time rift.

513
00:34:20,000 --> 00:34:21,240
It's the future.

514
00:34:21,880 --> 00:34:25,400
Listen. I brought you here
to keep you safe but it happened again.

515
00:34:27,480 --> 00:34:29,920
You died again.

516
00:34:30,000 --> 00:34:31,760
What do you mean, again?

517
00:34:33,360 --> 00:34:34,760
(SIGHS)

518
00:34:36,520 --> 00:34:38,160
(SNARLING)

519
00:34:47,360 --> 00:34:48,960
Hang on.

520
00:34:49,040 --> 00:34:52,480
As long as we interrupt the time line,
this can't happen.

521
00:34:54,960 --> 00:34:58,000
Don't touch each other. Otherwise,
the future will reassert itself.

522
00:35:02,080 --> 00:35:03,640
Gregor!

523
00:35:03,720 --> 00:35:05,680
Gregor, let go of the circuit.

524
00:35:06,560 --> 00:35:08,280
-Just let it go!
-Gregor!

525
00:35:09,120 --> 00:35:10,440
Gregor!

526
00:35:16,480 --> 00:35:17,840
DOCTOR: Come on.

527
00:35:29,080 --> 00:35:30,560
Okay.

528
00:35:31,720 --> 00:35:33,520
Uh... Okay.

529
00:35:47,480 --> 00:35:49,240
(GROANING)

530
00:35:50,000 --> 00:35:51,480
Tricky!

531
00:35:51,920 --> 00:35:54,680
No! Don't touch him
or time will reassert itself!

532
00:35:56,000 --> 00:35:57,440
(BOTH GROANING)

533
00:36:13,280 --> 00:36:16,240
The engine room.
The heart of the Tardis.

534
00:36:17,880 --> 00:36:19,600
(SCREAMS) We're outside.

535
00:36:19,680 --> 00:36:21,320
No. We're still in the Tardis.

536
00:36:21,400 --> 00:36:23,600
-There's no way across.
-No, okay. You're right.

537
00:36:23,680 --> 00:36:25,800
So, what do we do? Time for a plan.
Do you have a plan?

538
00:36:25,880 --> 00:36:28,400
Well...no. No plan, sorry.

539
00:36:28,480 --> 00:36:32,000
-If you don't have a plan, we're dead.
-Yes, we are.

540
00:36:32,080 --> 00:36:33,800
-So, just tell me.
-Tell you what?

541
00:36:33,880 --> 00:36:35,280
Well, there's no point now.

542
00:36:35,360 --> 00:36:37,360
We're about to die.
Just tell me who you are.

543
00:36:37,440 --> 00:36:38,880
-You know who I am.
-No, I don't.

544
00:36:38,960 --> 00:36:41,680
I look at you every single day and I
don't understand a thing about you.

545
00:36:41,760 --> 00:36:44,040
Why do I keep running into you?

546
00:36:44,120 --> 00:36:46,440
-Doctor, you invited me. You said...
-Before that.

547
00:36:46,520 --> 00:36:48,920
I met you at the Dalek asylum.
There was a girl in a shipwreck

548
00:36:49,000 --> 00:36:51,000
and she died saving my life
and she was you.

549
00:36:51,080 --> 00:36:52,120
She really wasn't.

550
00:36:52,200 --> 00:36:54,440
Victorian London. There was a governess
who was really a barmaid

551
00:36:54,520 --> 00:36:56,120
and we fought
the Great Intelligence together.

552
00:36:56,200 --> 00:36:59,560
She died and it was my fault.
And she was you!

553
00:36:59,640 --> 00:37:00,920
-You're scaring me.
-What are you, eh?

554
00:37:01,000 --> 00:37:04,080
-A trick? A trap?
-I don't know what you're talking about!

555
00:37:13,680 --> 00:37:15,040
You really don't, do you?

556
00:37:15,120 --> 00:37:16,360
I think I'm more scared
of you right now

557
00:37:16,440 --> 00:37:17,680
than anything else on that Tardis.

558
00:37:17,760 --> 00:37:21,760
You're just Clara, aren't you?
Eh? Huh? (CHUCKLING)

559
00:37:21,840 --> 00:37:23,440
Oh!

560
00:37:24,160 --> 00:37:28,080
Okay. I don't know what the hell this
is about but the hug is really nice.

561
00:37:32,240 --> 00:37:33,800
We're not going to die here.

562
00:37:33,880 --> 00:37:35,360
This isn't real.

563
00:37:37,080 --> 00:37:38,560
-It's a snarl.
-What?

564
00:37:38,640 --> 00:37:41,360
What does a wounded animal do?
It tries to scare everyone away.

565
00:37:41,440 --> 00:37:44,880
We're close to the engine.
The Tardis is snarling at us,

566
00:37:44,960 --> 00:37:46,760
trying to frighten us off.

567
00:37:46,840 --> 00:37:48,360
We need to jump.

568
00:37:48,440 --> 00:37:51,040
-You're insane.
-We'll cross the portal to the engine.

569
00:37:51,480 --> 00:37:52,920
-How can you be so sure?
-Well, I can't.

570
00:37:53,000 --> 00:37:54,120
Okay, then, well, that's watertight.

571
00:37:54,200 --> 00:37:56,360
Hey, now, Clara.
I have piloted this ship

572
00:37:56,440 --> 00:37:59,640
for over 900 years.
Trust me this one time, please.

573
00:38:01,600 --> 00:38:04,200
Okay. Okay.

574
00:38:04,280 --> 00:38:06,200
As well as all the other times.

575
00:38:06,800 --> 00:38:08,440
Ready?

576
00:38:08,520 --> 00:38:09,920
Geronimo.

577
00:38:11,400 --> 00:38:12,920
(BOTH SCREAMING)

578
00:38:20,760 --> 00:38:22,960
The heart of the Tardis.

579
00:38:24,760 --> 00:38:26,200
The engine.

580
00:38:26,720 --> 00:38:29,920
It's already exploded. It must have been
the collision with the salvage ship.

581
00:38:30,000 --> 00:38:32,000
CLARA: We're not dead.

582
00:38:34,880 --> 00:38:37,160
She wrapped her hands around the force.

583
00:38:38,920 --> 00:38:40,560
-Froze it.
-So...

584
00:38:41,160 --> 00:38:42,800
So it's safe.

585
00:38:43,480 --> 00:38:48,040
Temporary fix.
Eventually, this whole place will erupt.

586
00:38:49,040 --> 00:38:51,880
There's no way I can save her now.

587
00:38:57,480 --> 00:39:00,680
She's just always been there for me
and taken care of me

588
00:39:00,760 --> 00:39:02,440
and now it's my turn
and I don't know what to do.

589
00:39:02,520 --> 00:39:04,160
(STUTTERING) It just...

590
00:39:14,560 --> 00:39:17,120
Oh, Clara.

591
00:39:17,880 --> 00:39:19,680
Oh.

592
00:39:21,000 --> 00:39:23,880
-You are beautiful.
-(CLARA CHUCKLES)

593
00:39:23,960 --> 00:39:27,520
Beautiful, fragile, human skin.

594
00:39:27,600 --> 00:39:29,760
Like parchment, thank you.

595
00:39:29,840 --> 00:39:31,960
The rift in time,
all the memory's leaking out.

596
00:39:32,040 --> 00:39:33,400
I need to find the moment we crashed.

597
00:39:33,480 --> 00:39:35,280
I need to find...

598
00:39:38,560 --> 00:39:39,840
the music.

599
00:39:41,440 --> 00:39:43,120
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

600
00:39:47,640 --> 00:39:48,920
The time rift!

601
00:39:49,000 --> 00:39:51,320
Recent past, possible future.

602
00:39:51,400 --> 00:39:53,760
-What are you going to do?
-Rewrite today, I hope.

603
00:39:53,840 --> 00:39:55,960
I've thrown this through
the rift before.

604
00:39:56,040 --> 00:39:59,840
I need to make sure this time,
going to take it in there myself.

605
00:40:01,080 --> 00:40:02,120
There might be
a certain amount of yelling.

606
00:40:02,200 --> 00:40:03,280
It's going to hurt?

607
00:40:03,360 --> 00:40:05,400
Things that end your life often do that.

608
00:40:05,480 --> 00:40:06,760
Wait!

609
00:40:07,280 --> 00:40:09,000
All those things you said.

610
00:40:09,080 --> 00:40:12,000
How we've met before, how I died...

611
00:40:12,080 --> 00:40:13,720
Clara, don't worry.

612
00:40:14,520 --> 00:40:16,680
You'll forget. Time mends us.
It can mend anything.

613
00:40:16,760 --> 00:40:19,480
I don't want to forget. Not all of it.

614
00:40:20,960 --> 00:40:23,480
The library. I saw it.

615
00:40:24,200 --> 00:40:26,520
You were mentioned in a book.

616
00:40:26,600 --> 00:40:28,480
I'm mentioned in a lot of books.

617
00:40:30,520 --> 00:40:32,880
You call yourself Doctor.
Why do you do that?

618
00:40:32,960 --> 00:40:37,000
You have a name. I've seen it
in one corner of that tiny...

619
00:40:37,560 --> 00:40:41,120
If I rewrite today, you won't remember.
You won't go looking

620
00:40:41,200 --> 00:40:43,040
for my name.

621
00:40:43,800 --> 00:40:48,200
-We'll still have secrets?
-Uh-huh. It's better that way.

622
00:40:52,640 --> 00:40:53,640
Whoo!

623
00:40:54,520 --> 00:40:56,040
(SCREAMS)

624
00:40:57,360 --> 00:40:59,080
(SCREAMING)

625
00:41:05,880 --> 00:41:07,360
(EXCLAIMING)

626
00:41:07,440 --> 00:41:11,400
Magnetic Hubble field!
We're flying right into it.

627
00:41:12,320 --> 00:41:14,400
Clara! Stay by me!

628
00:41:14,960 --> 00:41:17,240
Please tell me there's a button
you can press to fix this.

629
00:41:17,320 --> 00:41:19,440
Oh, yes. Big friendly button.

630
00:41:19,520 --> 00:41:21,160
-You're lying.
-Yeah.

631
00:41:21,240 --> 00:41:23,280
-To stop me freaking out?
-Oh, is it working?

632
00:41:23,360 --> 00:41:24,920
-Not so much!
-(DOCTOR SCREAMING)

633
00:41:30,880 --> 00:41:32,680
Doctor. Doctor.

634
00:41:32,760 --> 00:41:34,640
I'm from your future.

635
00:41:35,400 --> 00:41:38,320
We haven't got long. This'll reset time.

636
00:41:42,360 --> 00:41:43,880
(DOCTOR SCREAMING)

637
00:41:50,160 --> 00:41:53,600
Clara! No! No!

638
00:41:59,240 --> 00:42:01,480
(CHUCKLING) Big friendly button.

639
00:42:18,360 --> 00:42:20,880
I don't get it.
It was on-screen, then it was gone.

640
00:42:20,960 --> 00:42:23,000
BRAM: Hey, robot!
Go get me some food.

641
00:42:23,080 --> 00:42:24,200
I'm starving.

642
00:42:24,280 --> 00:42:26,120
Oi. Leave him alone.

643
00:42:26,200 --> 00:42:27,360
What's the matter with you?

644
00:42:27,440 --> 00:42:29,920
Maybe I've just got
a little tiny scrap of decency.

645
00:42:30,000 --> 00:42:31,400
(SCOFFS)

646
00:42:51,840 --> 00:42:53,280
I feel exhausted. I feel...

647
00:42:53,360 --> 00:42:55,920
We've had two days
crammed into the space of one.

648
00:42:56,320 --> 00:42:59,040
-Why would you say that?
-I don't know. I say stuff.

649
00:42:59,120 --> 00:43:00,520
Ignore me.

650
00:43:02,360 --> 00:43:03,800
Do you feel safe?

651
00:43:05,160 --> 00:43:06,560
Of course.

652
00:43:08,200 --> 00:43:09,960
Give me a number out of 10,

653
00:43:10,040 --> 00:43:13,320
10 being "whoo-hoo!”, one being...

654
00:43:13,960 --> 00:43:16,440
-"ahhh!"
-You're being weird.

655
00:43:16,520 --> 00:43:19,120
I need to know if you feel safe.
I need to know...

656
00:43:20,200 --> 00:43:22,000
-you're not afraid.
-Of?

657
00:43:22,720 --> 00:43:24,080
The future.

658
00:43:24,160 --> 00:43:27,240
Running away with a spaceman in a box.
Anything could happen to you.

659
00:43:27,320 --> 00:43:29,560
That's what I'm counting on.

660
00:43:29,640 --> 00:43:30,960
Push the button.

661
00:43:43,640 --> 00:43:46,120
We are going to the North.

662
00:43:47,040 --> 00:43:51,320
Sweetville. An ideal community
for happy, prosperous workers.

663
00:43:51,480 --> 00:43:55,080
No one who ever goes to live there
ever seems to come out.

664
00:43:55,160 --> 00:43:57,840
I suspect all is not quite as it seems.

665
00:43:57,920 --> 00:43:59,520
Time for a plan.

666
00:43:59,600 --> 00:44:03,040
You do seem to keep turning up
like a bad penny, young man.

667
00:44:03,120 --> 00:44:05,800
The Crimson Horror.
That's what they're calling it.

668
00:44:06,280 --> 00:44:08,120
My plans must be accelerated.

669
00:44:08,200 --> 00:44:10,080
Mrs Gillyflower, we've got to stop her.

670
00:44:10,160 --> 00:44:14,720
In the wrong hands, that venom
could wipe out all life on this planet.

